26/10/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- A new poll was released suggesting Prime Minister Adrian Nastase is the favourite in the 28 November presidential elections. The survey, by the Data Media agency, found 40 per cent of respondents supported Nastase, compared to 33 per cent for Bucharest Mayor Traian Basescu. 
Also Monday, Lieutenant General Eugen Badalan was appointed as the new chief of the Army's General Staff on Monday (25 October). He has served as deputy chief since 2000.(Gardianul, Nine o'clock - 26/10/04; Rompres - 25/10/04)
